name: but, I'm sure there's something in a shade of grey
description:
Dimensions: 9 x 12 x 1.5 inches
Year: 2013

The inspiration for this piece was from a photograph that I took of my sister-in-law a few years ago. I've always loved the photo, and this painting just kind of unfolded organically. I like the idea of a color representing someone being enveloped by the space they are in, and that's what this piece is about...the weight of space. 

For me, Grey is such a powerful color. There is a heaviness to it that I just love and it's my favorite color to paint with.


This is an original oil painting on wood panel. It is 9 x 12 inches and has a 1.5 inch border. The sides have been painted grey to match the background so it is ready to hang (no need for a frame)
